<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 6:13PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Cherokee and southwestern Pickens Counties through 645 PM EDT...
At 613 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Salacoa Valley, or 9
miles southwest of Jasper, moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Canton, Holly Springs, Waleska, Lake Arrowhead, Salacoa Valley,
Talmadge, Sutallee, Bridgemill and Hickory Flat.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
